RIYADH: Riyadh Governor Prince Faisal bin Bandar is set to attend the sixth King Abdulaziz Award for Quality ceremony, and the forum for Best Practices in Quality and Institutional Excellence, the Saudi Press Agency has reported. The awards ceremony, which takes place in Riyadh on Jan. 16, will honor 15 recipients achieving the highest standards of quality from the government, private, and non-profit sectors. The forum, which runs for two days from Jan. 17, will discuss concepts of quality and its role in developing institutional performance in line with the Kingdomâ€™s Vision 2030. It will cover areas such as quality of life, sustainable development, management, and improving the quality of operations and services. 